Started this project on the 3rd of this month. I was inspired by a video that I saw
on YouTube by a Senior Engineer who had decades of experience coding. His recommendation
is to create a pipeline with an architect and builder agent. I am aware that creating
agents with separate functions is considered the gold standard when using agentic
workflows to generate software solutions. However, this is my first attempt at building
my own pipeline. I am taking it slow, giving myself until September to officially launch
the pipeline, so that I don't rush into production. Since this is the factory of my code,
the very foundation upon which all other things will be built, I want it to be stable, 
efficient, no-nonsense & purposeful. 

Day 1: On July 3rd, I created the architect + builder blueprint and created the prompt
for the architect builder. I am going to refine the architect as much as possible &
experiment with as many models as necessary to get a beautiful agent that works flawlessly
to design the blueprint for the code. 

All other agents are barred from coding. 

Day 2: Built the /pipeline directory & some subfolders. Focusing on the think tank, otherwise
known as the research team for my build. This will be comprised of 3 agents:

1: SCUBA - data dog
2: MOZART - composer and synthesizer
3: PNUT - The judge; named after my dear friend Ronald Hibbard, who passed away. RIP Ronnie. 
          You are missed, but never forgotten. This one's for you, homie. Love you dude.

Day 3: Built the SOUL.md for SCUBA, MOZART, and PNUT. Currently working on the scripts
to chain them together beautifully into a wonderful orchestra. 